Renamed 1.7.1980 to become the parish of Caddington & Slip End. 
    See also Table 2, notes (b) and (d).

Created 1.7.1980 by renaming the parish of Caddington. See also 
    Table 2, note (l).

Abolished 1.4.1974 to become the South Bedfordshire unparished area. See also Table 
    2, note (b).

Created 1.4.1985 out of the South Beddfordshire unparished area and 
    the parishes of Caddington & Slip End, Houghton Regis, Kensworth and 
    Totternhoe. See also Table 2, note (l).

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parish of 
    Dunstable. Abolished 1.4.1985 and divided between the parishes of Dunstable 
    and Houghton Regis.
